 <div class="travel itinerary">
    <h2><font color="#800080">Travel itinerary</font></h2>
   
   <p><br></p>
   
   <p><strong>- 1st Stop: United States - New York</strong></p>
   <p><font color="#800080">-Broadway:</font>
   Watching a Broadway musical is one of the most popular activities for Brazilians traveling to New York. These are grand, over-produced presentations that truly provide unforgettable experiences.</p>
    
   
   <p><font color="#800080">-National Museum of Indians:</font>
   Part of a branch of the Smithsonian Institute in New York, the museum is housed in a beautiful building near Battery Park. There are more than 825,000 items from 1,200 indigenous cultures, covering 12,000 years of history of the native peoples of the United States. It is one of the largest collections of its kind in the world and essential for understanding a little of the territory before the arrival of Europeans.</p>
   
   <img src="img/bro.jpg" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   <img src="img/museu.webp" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   
   <p><br></p>
   
   <p><strong>- 2nd Stop: Canada - Montreal</strong></p>
   
   <p><font color="#800080">-Montreal Boanic Garden:</font>
   Discover the Montreal Botanical Garden, one of the largest botanical gardens in the world. Nature lovers will be enchanted by the more than 22 thousand species of plants, 10 exhibition greenhouses and 20 themed gardens throughout its 75 hectares of fresh air and natural beauty.</p>
   
   <p><font color="#800080">-Notre Dame Basilica:</font>
   The Notre-Dame de Montreal Basilica is one of the most incredible buildings in the city and should not be left out of your itinerary. It is one of the main churches in Montreal and is dedicated to the Virgin Mary.
   The basilica is very large and has a really beautiful architecture, but it is its altar that takes visitors' breath away, in this space the highlight is the carved wood of the altar and painted in blue and gold. The space is magnificent and worth a photo.</p>
   
   <img src="img/jardim.jpg" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   <img src="img/basilica.avif" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   
   <p><br></p>

   <p><strong>- 3rd Stop: England - London</strong></p>

   <p><font color="#800080">-Tower of London:</font>
   Situated on the banks of the River Thames, the Tower of London is one of the city's most popular tourist attractions because of the mix of intrigue and dread inspired by its history. You will have the opportunity to see magnificent royal pieces that you have probably seen in magazines countless times.
   
   <p><font color="#800080">-Buckingham Palace:</font>
   Built in 1703 as the residence of the Duke of Buckingham, the palace now serves as the official residence of the British monarch, Charles III. It is a luxurious palace with stunning rooms, offices and beautiful gardens. Buckingham Palace has over 775 bedrooms, including 19 state bedrooms, 52 royal and guest bedrooms, 92 offices and 78 bathrooms. You can explore various sections of the building and check out the State Rooms, Throne Room, Ballroom, Grand Staircase, White Drawing Room, and the Queen's Gallery, among others.</p>
   
   <img src="img/torre.webp" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   <img src="img/palacio.jpeg" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   
   <p><br></p>
   
   <p><strong>- 4th Stop: South Africa - Cape Town</strong></p>
    
   <p><font color="#800080">-Green Point:</font>
   Built on the edge of the ocean, Green Point has already become one of Cape Town's postcards, another of the stadiums built specifically for the 2010 World Cup, Green Point is considered one of the most beautiful in South Africa With a capacity for 70,000 spectators, the venue, which is actually a multi-use arena, can host shows and other large events and is completely covered with a noise-reducing layer. </p>
   
   <p><font color="#800080">-Green Point:</font>
   Boulders Beach is a friendly beach with crystal clear, calm waters in Cape Town, and the most visited in the region, being the only place in the world where you can get this close to African penguins!</p>
   
   <img src="img/estadio.jpg" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   <img src="img/pinguin.jpg" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
   
    <p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>
    
    <div class="about the cruise">
        <h2><font color="#800080">How does the cost of the trip work?</font></h2>
       
        <p>Everything is included, <strong>except</strong> expenses at destinations, meals at cruise restaurants, SPA and gym</p>
       
        <p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>
       
        <div class="about the cruise">
        <h2>ATTENTION</h2>
       
       <p><strong>Pay attention to the times established by the ship for disembarking and boarding at each destination, as well as the optional activities and excursions offered on board</strong></p>
       
       <p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>
       
        <div class="about the cruise">
        <h2><font color="#800080">Boarding day</font></h2>

        <p>- The cruise will leave the Pier Mauá Maritime Terminal at 6:00 am, arrive at the boarding port in advance, at least 2 hours before</p>

        <p><strong>Rio de Janeiro - Pier Maúa Maritime Terminal</strong></p>
        <img src="img/mapa.png" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
        
        <p><br></p>
        
        <p>- Check in, present your intermediate or advanced English course certificate, collect your identification bracelet, and board the ship.</p>
        <p>- Check your cabin number and settle in</p>
        <p>- Have your breakfast from 06:30 to 07:30</p>
        <p>- Disembark at 08:00 with our local guide, and participate in our organized excursions, discover the tourist attractions presented. After this activity you are free to explore the city as you wish, getting to know the culture, typical local foods or shopping</p>
        <p>- Return to the ship at 6:30 pm for departure, don't forget to present your ID</p>
        <p>- In the evening, enjoy the ship's facilities and relax.</p>
        
<p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>

        <div class="about the cruise">
            <h2><font color="#800080">About the ID bracelet</font></h2>
        
        <p>Each passenger receives a bracelet with a unique code. Before the cruise begins, passenger data is recorded and programmed into our access control system, where we monitor the status of each passenger in real time, facilitating entry and exit monitoring.</p>
        <p>There are wristband reading machines installed at our arrival and departure gates.
        In addition, it is used to make payments within the cruise, access cabins and record activities carried out on the ship. Providing agility, safety, and greater performance for our passengers</p>
        
        <img src="img/pulseira.jpg" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="400">
        
        <p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>


        <div class="about the cruise">
            <h2><font color="#800080">Last day of navigation</font></h2>
           <p>- Enjoy the last day of sailing.</p>
           <p>- Take part in our activities</p>
           <p>- Enjoy special meals on board.</p>
           <p>- At 5:00 pm everyone must go to the meeting room, where they will receive their certificates</p>
           <p>- When the meeting ends, enjoy the night, dance in the disco, and watch the big closing show.</p>
           
           <p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>
           
           <div class="about the cruise">
            <h2><font color="#800080">Disembarkation</font></h2><div class="about the cruise">
            
           <p>- Prepare your bags and disembark the ship after breakfast.</p>
           <p>- When disembarking, return your identification bracelet</p>
           <p>- Thank the crew for their service.</p>
           <p>- Return to the embarkation port, and return home </p>
           <p>- We will rate you and come back whenever you want</p>

<p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>

