   <div class="about the course">
    <h2><font color="#800080">About the course</font></h2>
   
   <p>- We will offer mandatory and optional classes </p>
   <p>- We will make course support material available during classes, such as handouts and books, to help you continue practicing English outside the cruise</p>
   <p>- Inside the ship there will be communicative activities, such as workshops, sports, casino, shows, lectures, cooking classes, cinema, spa, restaurants, all using English, which will add to your knowledge of the language</p>
   <p>- Stops at destinations, where you can communicate with natives and practice your English</p>
   <p>- After the end of the trip we will send you your online certificate and your points achieved during the activities</p>
   
   <p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>

   <div class="Classes">
    <h2><font color="#800080">Classes and teachers</font></h2>
   
<p>English classes are <strong>mandatory</strong>, and take place from Monday to Saturday, from 8:00 am to 11:00 am. There are more than 10 with academic backgrounds in teaching English, as a foreign language and experience. Within these classes there are English immersion programs and related activities, such as conversation, pronunciation, reading and writing, providing interactive classes.

<p><br></p>

<p><strong>Are you tired of the same English exercises? So, meet Teacher Paula Gabriela</strong></p>
<p>One of the teachers who has grown the most in recent years, teaching on large platforms. Teacher Paula Gabriela started to develop a new way of teaching English, which is more practical and fun, using films, series, music and travel</p>

<img src="img/prof1.png" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="600">

<p> <br/><br/><br/> </p>


<div class="Classes">
    <h2><font color="#800080">Lectures</font></h2>

<p>Lectures are also <strong>mandatory</strong>. Our speakers are highly qualified and experienced, they cover a variety of topics such as vocabulary, grammar, pronunciation, idioms and culture.
During the Lectures, participants have the opportunity to practice their English conversation skills by participating in interactive exercises and group discussions. Let's get to know a little about one of our guest speakers?</p>

<p><br></p>

<p><strong>It's quite common to notice Brazilians interested in learning English, but have you ever thought about how it works the other way around?</strong></p>
<p>What if I told you that an American named Gavin Roy became fluent in Portuguese on his own?
    It seems impossible, but it's true! So, becoming fluent in English is also possible, this is the promise of Gavin Roy, one of the leading English teachers on the market. And to find out if all this is true, we prepared an exclusive talk with him on our cruise.</p>

    <img src="img/prof2.jpeg" alt="cruzeiro" height="315" width="600">

